09<h2>If you are the website administrator:</h2>\x0a\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<p>You may now add content to the webroot directory. Note\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09that until you do so, people visiting your website will see\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09this page, and not your content.</p>\x0a\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<p>For systems using the Apache HTTP Server:\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09You may now add content to the directory <tt>/var/www/html/</tt>. Note that until you do so, people visiting your website will see this page, and not your content. To prevent this page from ever being used, follow the instructions in the file <tt>/etc/httpd/conf.d/welcome.conf</tt>.</p>\x0a\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<p>For systems using NGINX:\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09You should now put your content in a location of your\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09choice and edit the <code>root</code> configuration directive\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09in the <strong>nginx</strong> configuration file\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<code>/etc/nginx/nginx.conf</code>.</p>\x0a\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<div class="logos">\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<a href="https://almalinux.org"><img src= "/icons/poweredby.png" alt="[ Powered by AlmaLinux ]" /></a>\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09<img src= "poweredby.png" alt="[ Powered by AlmaLinux ]" />\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09\x09</div>\x0a\x09\x09\x09\x09</div>\x0a\x09\x09\x09</div>\x0a\x09\x09</div>\x0a\x09<div class="footer">\x0a\x09\x09<a href="https://apache.org">Apache&trade;</a> is a registered trademark of <a href="https://apache.org">the Apache Software Foundation</a> in the United States and/or other countries.\x0a        <br />\x0a\x09\x09<a href="https://nginx.com">NGINX&trade;</a> is a registered trademark of <a href="https://www.f5.com">F5 Networks, Inc.</a>.\x0a\x09</div>\x0a\x09</body>\x0a</html>\x0a

